 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","title":"CI coverage gate workflow + threshold checker","description":"Implement CI workflow that computes coverage metrics and enforces approved thresholds with actionable failure output. Output: gate job plus summary annotations.","design":"Use one threshold checker implementation consumed by local and CI contexts to prevent divergent pass/fail logic.","acceptance_criteria":"- Workflow computes required coverage metrics and validates against policy config without manual interpretation.
- Failure output identifies exact threshold breaches and affected invariant areas.
- Job logs are structured and include links/paths to raw coverage artifacts.","notes":"Include guardrails for transient tooling failures so infrastructure noise is distinguishable from true coverage regression. Unit-shard consistency alignment is validated in bd-mblr.3.1.2 rather than blocking initial coverage-gate workflow implementation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.393247946Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:25.976326114Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.215917312Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:37.961549887Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.393247946Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","title":"Invariant-matrix unit coverage drift CI gate","description":"Add CI checker that compares current unit-test evidence against the invariant matrix and fails on critical-path regressions, missing invariant assertions, or mock-only regressions for required unit lanes. Output: deterministic drift report with actionable diffs.","design":"Generate deterministic coverage-drift evidence from invariant matrix artifacts and unit CI outputs, then apply policy thresholds from coverage/no-mock SLO definitions.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI compares current unit evidence against invariant matrix and fails on critical-path drift, missing assertions, or forbidden mock-only regressions. 2. Drift report is deterministic and includes direct links to failing invariants/tests. 3. Gate integrates with flake policy without masking true regressions.","notes":"This gate is implemented before final flake-policy finalization; flake/quarantine policy (bd-mblr.3.3) then codifies handling based on observed gate behavior.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.014075415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:26.080396091Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.984727490Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.014075415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.161981880Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.708894721Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.433463864Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.2","title":"CI E2E Matrix and Artifact Upload Gate","description":"Run required e2e matrix lanes in CI (correctness/recovery/concurrency tiers) and upload structured logs plus repro bundles as artifacts on failure.","design":"Use scenario matrix metadata as single source for lane generation to avoid manual workflow drift.","acceptance_criteria":"- Required E2E matrix lanes (correctness/recovery/concurrency/compat) run in CI with deterministic seeds.
- Failure artifact upload includes logs, seed manifest, scenario IDs, and replay instructions.
- Matrix includes explicit pass/fail policy for required vs optional lanes.","notes":"E2E gate track now combines matrix execution/artifact durability (bd-mblr.3.2.1) with scenario-to-script drift detection (bd-mblr.3.2.2), ensuring required scenarios remain both mapped and executed with reproducible evidence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:58.297984521Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.580691529Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.844209325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:42:38.530941313Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1349,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CI artifact policy: on failure, upload logs + reduced repro + mismatch diagnostics + environment manifest. Artifacts must be sufficient for offline replay by another engineer/agent.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:13Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","title":"CI E2E matrix workflow + artifact publishing","description":"Implement CI matrix for scenario workloads with deterministic seeds and durable artifact upload policy. Output: reproducible matrix runs with retained diagnostics.","design":"Implement matrix definition as data (manifest) plus renderer, not hand-authored duplicated YAML blocks.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI matrix generation is deterministic and traceable to canonical scenario/seed manifests.
